==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caducous
<hw>Ca*du"cous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[L. <ets>caducus</ets> falling,
inclined to fall, fr. <ets>cadere</ets> to fall. See
<er>Cadence</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Dropping off or
disappearing early, as the calyx of a poppy, or the gills of a
tadpole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caduke</ent>⟦br⟧
